Amazing Energy Oil & Gas Co. Announces the Completion and Production of the WWJD #13 Well | Business Wire


























































      Amazing Energy Oil & Gas Co. Announces the Completion and Production of 
      the WWJD #13 Well
    





January 06, 2015 08:00 AM Eastern Standard Time



SPOKANE, Wash.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Terry Dunne, Chairman and CEO of Amazing Energy Oil & Gas Co. (“GCMN” on 
      the OTCBB) is pleased to announce The Company has drilled and completed 
      the WWJD #13 well, which was first announced on November 12, 2014. The 
      well was fracked on Monday, December 29, 2014 using a new fracking 
      technique that The Company first implemented in 2014. The operator 
      reported to the Railroad Commission in its Initial Production Completion 
      Report dated December 31, 2014 that the well produced 148 barrels of oil 
      and 122 MCF on an initial 24 hour flow test. The operator’s update on 
      Monday, January 5, 2015 reported that the well continued to flow between 
      120 and 130 BOPD and has produced approximately 1,082 BBLS since coming 
      online last month. The Railroad Commission has given the operator 
      approval to sell the first 5,000 barrels of oil on a P8 permit.
    

      Mr. Dunne stated that, “The Company will continue to develop the 
      approximate 70,000 acre Pecos County, Texas leasehold with plans of 
      expanding drilling operations into adjacent sections soon. We are very 
      excited about our recent success in our shallow-well project. The 
      Company continues to be a low cost per barrel producer. Unlike the shale 
      plays that might cost several millions of dollars per well, our wells 
      cost approximately $400,000. We utilize conventional drilling techniques 
      in legacy producing, shallow formations that are usually less than 2,000 
      ft deep, giving us an advantage during these times of price volatility, 
      and allowing us to grow, while others are shutting down.”
    

      According to Mr. Dunne, “Amazing Energy Oil and Gas Co. currently owns 
      interests in 18 wells in the Permian Basin. Although not all 18 wells 
      are currently operating, we will be bringing them online as we continue 
      to build our infrastructure, adding more gas lines and electric service. 
      This is a very large project and we are focused on getting it up and 
      running as quickly as we can. The WWJD #13 is another great addition 
      toward accomplishing this goal.”
    

      Please also reference our website at amazingenergy.com.
    

      This Press Release contains certain forward-looking statements and our 
      future operating results could differ materially from those discussed 
      herein. Certain statements contained in this Report, including, without 
      limitation, statements containing the words “believes,” “anticipates,” 
      “expects” and the like, constitute “forward-looking statements”. Such 
      forward-looking statements involve known and unknown risks, 
      uncertainties and other factors which may cause our actual results, 
      performance or achievements to be materially different from any future 
      results, performance or achievements expressed or implied by such 
      forward-looking statements. Given these uncertainties, readers are 
      cautioned not to place undue reliance on such forward-looking 
      statements. We disclaim any obligation to update any such factors or to 
      announce publicly the results of any revisions of the forward-looking 
      statements contained or incorporated by reference herein to reflect 
      future events or developments.
    

      Contact:Amazing Energy Oil & Gas Co.Terry Dunne, (509) 
      462-0315Chairman and CEOTerry@amazingenergy.com





Contacts

      Amazing Energy Oil & Gas Co.Terry Dunne, 509-462-0315Chairman 
      and CEOTerry@amazingenergy.com













Contacts

      Amazing Energy Oil & Gas Co.Terry Dunne, 509-462-0315Chairman 
      and CEOTerry@amazingenergy.com







 
 

 






